RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Turf CR: 79. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ILLHAVEANOTHERKISS broke a step slow then was coaxed to the front, cleared and moved inside, saved ground through the turn, put to right handed urging with a furlong remaining and remained clear to the wire. SATOSHI broke alertly then was closest in pursuit of the leader up the backstretch, chased two wide then between rivals into the stretch, finished willingly despite needing more and held the place. DUSTY SPRINGFIELD broke a step slow, settled off the pace and moved inside, saved ground through the turn, lacked room behind rivals in upper stretch, altered out at the eighth pole and rallied only to miss the place. GRAZEN TOUCH stalked three deep into and around the turn, finished evenly late and was outkicked for the place and show. MAGIC WANDERER sat off the pace, rounded the bend three then four wide and could not rally. BLONDZILLA stalked from inside, coaxed along on the turn continuing to save ground, asked right handed into the stretch and weakened. HEY DEMPS off slow to begin, pulled the rider into range, chased two then three wide on the turn and weakened. STYLISH DRESS broke a step slow, trailed outside a rival early, traveled two wide then angled in late on the bend and made no impact.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THOMPSON stumbled a bit but still came away quickest, dueled from outside around the first turn, chased VERITAS AEQUITAS up the backstretch, bid between rivals at the seven-sixteenths pole, dueled inside UNCLE JUJU around that bend, shook free entering the stretch and widened under a drive. RINGTONE stalked three wide then moved into the two path, angled to the inside and was coaxed along into the far turn, tipped three wide and was asked around the bend, moved out further in the lane and bested the rest. VERITAS AEQUITAS broke cleanly but was asked to get going early and hustled up to the front from inside, dueled around the first turn, cleared early on the backstretch, challenged by a pair of rivals into the far turn, lost command with three furlongs left to run, chased the leaders to the stretch, weakened in the lane but churned on to save the show honors. UNCLE JUJU got brushed from inside and had the rider lose his iron briefly at the start before regaining footing, prominent early into the first turn then got put in tight between rivals and had to take up, moved out to the three path, chased up the backstretch, bid three deep into the far turn, dueled outside THOMPSON around that bend, could not kick on with the winner entering the stretch and weakened down the lane. SCREAMING VIRGINIA brushed lightly with UNCLE JUJU leaving the gate, trailed two wide then along the rail early, angled four wide around the second bend and was not a factor.

THIRTY CARATS stepped to the front and controlled the pace along the inside through the early going, met the bid from outer rival on the far turn, cleared when roused in upper stretch, put to right handed urging shortly after, switch to the left hand midstretch but could not fend off the winner in the late stages. BEAUTIFUL BOLT stalked three then two wide on the clubhouse turn, remained off the rail and took aim three deep entering the stretch but finished evenly in the late stages. HAPPY HAPPY was off slow to begin, stalked on the inside, pushed on through the second bend, remained on the fence through the drive racing within striking distance but needed to find more late.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 92. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CIRCLE OF TRUST reserved in the two path, advanced three deep in the middle stages, bumped with inner rival into the far turn, drew closer around the bend and bid three deep entering the stretch, kicked clear midstretch and held safely under steady handling late. BLUE OASIS tracked in the two path outside a rival, went between foes on the backstretch, bumped with rivals on both sides into the far turn, continued to give chase in the two path to the lane, lacked room behind the leaders in upper stretch, altered out with a furlong remaining, finished gamely in deep stretch but could not get to the winner. VISUALLY settled inside off the pace, moved outside a rival on the backstretch, took the second bend two then three wide and gained the show. AVOIR broke out and brushed rival, forwardly placed three deep on the first turn, flanked the leader from outside in the middle stages, dueled around the far turn and took over leaving the bend, put away inner rival with a furlong left to run but overtaken by CIRCLE OF TRUST past the eighth pole and weakened late. GLO GLO showed good early speed to take control from inside, showed the way up the backstretch, dueled with AVOIR around the far turn, lost command leaving the bend and weakened in the furlong grounds. AMELIA BLEU bumped by AVOIR leaving the gate, tracked from inside early on, got blocked by MOTET and had to check entering the far turn, tipped out to the two path and could not rally. NAKOTA (IRE) was off slow to begin, tucked inside while lagging behind, trailed from the fence to the stretch, moved out in the lane and was not a factor. MOTET raced up close in the two path early, pressed briefly between into the backstretch then dropped back to a stalking position and moved inside, got bumped, put in tight while brushing the rail and took up into the far turn, saved ground to the lane had little left for the stretch. THERE WAS AN INQUIRY INVOLVING THE RUNNING INTO THE FAR TURN. AFTER A REVIEW, THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED CIRCLE OF TRUST FROM FIRST TO LAST FOR DRIFTING IN AND FORCING BLUE OASIS INTO MOTET, CAUSING MOTET TO TAKE UP AND COSTING HER A CHANCE AT A BETTER PLACING.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CANELO attended the pace three deep, roused on the far turn, took over past the quarter pole, cleared inner rivals entering the stretch, led under left handed encouragement into deep stretch and held safely. STAR PROSPECT steadied a bit between rivals while three wide on the first turn, went to wide into the second bend, spun four wide into the lane, finished willingly and edged TAKE CHARGE CURLY for the place honors. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A SWEEPSTAKES OF $60,000 AT ONE MILE OR OVER OTHER THAN STATE BRED IN 2023. The added monies and all fees to be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 12% to third, 6% to fourth and 2% to fifth. Three-year-olds 122 lbs. Older 126 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes at One Mile or Over allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of Two Races Other Than Maiden, Claiming or Starter at One Mile or Over allowed 4 lbs. (Rail at 30 feet).
